{"id":"project-LICHEN-uvda","title":"dispatch.rs: Response::content silently truncates payloads over 128 bytes","description":"File: rust/lichen-node/src/dispatch.rs:62-70

Response::content silently truncates payloads exceeding the 128-byte buffer without warning:

```rust
pub fn content(payload: &[u8]) -> Self {
    let mut resp = Self {
        code: MessageCode::CONTENT,
        content_format: Some(content_format::APPLICATION_CBOR),
        payload: [0u8; 128],
        payload_len: payload.len().min(128),  // Silent truncation
    };
    resp.payload[..resp.payload_len].copy_from_slice(&payload[..resp.payload_len]);
    resp
}
```

Impact: Resource handlers returning data >128 bytes will silently lose data. Callers have no indication that truncation occurred.

Fix: Either increase buffer size, return Result<Response, Error>, or log a warning when truncation occurs.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:35:16.014485Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:35:16.014529Z"}

